race.comment: Tricky. FALCON LAIR (1) resumes for a top Sydney stable and Collett's booking is a decent push for his chances. He missed 1L over at Goulburn at his only fresh outing and was spelled off a Maiden win there over a mile. Has two metro trials under the saddle and this is winnable if he's presented on song. Local gallopers fill the next three slots. WOLF ISLAND (5) resumed at Albury over shorter and looked a run short. He's presented off a heavily bet and deserved Maiden win over 1300m at this track. Keeps Jack Martin and can feature with the extra fitness. SHOWTIME MAGGIE (11) improved sharply winning her Maiden comfortably at Moruya. Keeps an in-form jockey and is sure to keep improving. Stablemate SHOREMAN (13) deserves consideration at a price. Has switched from the Matt Dale yard on a 185-day return and is a free runner drawn the inside barrier. Was last seen winning a Moruya Maiden and McDougall's booking sparks interest.
